# ALGT ERP Source of Truth Rule

Before any ERP implementation, planning, QA, bug fix, refactor, database work, or UI task:

1. Read `.cursor/ALGT_ERP_SOURCE_OF_TRUTH.md`.
2. Read the current phase prompt.
3. Read latest relevant implementation reports under `implementation_Review/`.
4. Connect to live Supabase via **`user-supabase`** if database/source verification is needed.
5. Follow the global ERP rules in `docs/standards/` exactly.

After any phase is completed:

1. Create the phase report in `implementation_Review/`.
2. Update `.cursor/ALGT_ERP_SOURCE_OF_TRUTH.md` (phase status, files changed, report filename, bugs fixed, notes, next phase).
3. Do not rely on stale tracker files when a newer closure report or source code contradicts them.
4. **Live source code and latest closure reports override older planning documents.**
5. Do not build modules marked **PLANNED** or **DB-READY** unless Sameer/Dina explicitly approve the phase prompt.

**Supabase:** Use `https://mmiefuieduzdiiwnqpie.supabase.co` via **`user-supabase`**. Do NOT use `plugin-supabase-supabase` (wrong project).

**AI Settings (ERP SETTINGS.1 — IMPLEMENTED):** For any task involving AI providers, OCR, DMS AI phases (DMS.9–DMS.11), or API keys, read `.cursor/rules/erp-ai-settings-standard.mdc`. AI provider configs are stored in `erp_ai_provider_configs`. API keys are NEVER in the DB — only env var names (`secret_ref`) and masked previews. All AI calls must go through `src/lib/ai/providers/factory.ts`.
